# {{.Name}} ({{.Type}})

{{ .Description | trimspace }}

This resource manages rules within a Microsoft Entra Global Secure Access content policy.

## Microsoft Documentation

Microsoft Graph beta metadata and Microsoft Learn do not currently expose the portal-backed `fileRule` type used by this resource. The implementation is based on Microsoft Entra admin center traffic and live Microsoft Graph beta verification.

## Microsoft Graph API

This resource uses:

```http
POST   /beta/networkaccess/filePolicies/{contentPolicyId}/policyRules
GET    /beta/networkaccess/filePolicies/{contentPolicyId}/policyRules/{ruleId}
PATCH  /beta/networkaccess/filePolicies/{contentPolicyId}/policyRules/{ruleId}
DELETE /beta/networkaccess/filePolicies/{contentPolicyId}/policyRules/{ruleId}
```

The Terraform destination types map to the following Graph discriminator values:

- `web_category`: `#microsoft.graph.networkaccess.filePolicyWebCategoryDestination`
- `fqdn`: `#microsoft.graph.networkaccess.filePolicyFqdnDestination`
- `url`: `#microsoft.graph.networkaccess.filePolicyUrlDestination`

## Microsoft Graph API Permissions

The following client `application` permissions are needed in order to use this {{.Type | lower}}:

**Required:**
- `NetworkAccess.Read.All`
- `NetworkAccess.ReadWrite.All`

**Optional:**
- `None` `[N/A]`

